args: Eight hostiles detected to the northwest!\nSuggesting a surprise attack from behind\nthat boulder. Deploy reinforcements!
Cover each other's blind spots and\nattack in unison! On my signal... Now!
That takes care of that.\nFinni was in top form again today.
She used to be much more...volatile?\nBut lately, I can rest easy letting her take\ncommand.
Yes... I'm very happy that you hold\nher in such high regard. I just...
The way she's fighting—how she\nstops and thinks? It's not like her.\nShe's like...a phantom from the past.
I'm back, Eirene. That does it for\nthis operation, I think.
Yes. But Finni, before the debriefing...\nAre you hiding something from me?
You've been acting...strangely. Almost\nlike you're trying to be a different person.
Oh, you noticed? Sorry; I haven't perfected\nthings yet, so I'm keeping my cards close\nto my chest for now.
But it's definitely something good for you,\nso turn that frown upside down! All I need\nyou to do is believe in me and hang tight.
Everything I do, I do for you, Eirene.
I detect hostiles to the north-northwest...\nand their signals unmistakably belong to\nEx Machina.
Truly?! That bodes ill.\nI shall make for them at once.

No, you can't. The signature I'm detecting
emits waves that are harmful to your
organic body. We androids will carry
out this operation alone.
Just leave it to us!\nC'mon, Eirene!
Hrk... There're even more of them than\nI expected. You hanging tight, Eirene?!
I'm fine. I've still got enough strength\nleft to destroy the enemy and then head\nback to the rest of our forces.
Focus on the immediate threat.\nI'll be done here before long.
An ambush! There were more of them?!
Stay calm! We can still handle a force of\nthis size. Find your composure and act!
Got it...! I'll be calm and cool-headed,\njust like her...
I've only sustained minor damage. I'll be\nfine. But we can't flip the script on this\nsituation with only the two of us.
While I buy you some time, I want you\nto go and get Laxi. Understood?
Oh...right. If SHE were here, she'd retreat.\nUnderstood. Commencing egress...
What are you doing, Finni?!\nHurry up and get going!
I know! I know I need to, but my body\nwon't do what I tell it! Dammit, why?!
I was doing so well until just now...\nThe old me wouldn't hesitate like this!
If I were her, I would retreat. But I just\ndon't want to go, no matter what I...
...Huh? Wait... Now I see.\n＂I don't want to go.＂
Why are you dawdling, Finni?\nWithdraw before it's too late!
I want to protect Eirene. Now and always.\nThat has always been my priority above\nall else!
Hrgh... You might THINK you have my\nnumber, but you don't! TAKE THIIIS!
No... This only happened because you\nprotected me! Why...why did you ignore\nmy command?!
I finally understand. I can't be anyone\nbut myself. I can't become her...
And that's why...I'm okay with it. It's okay\nif I'm not the Finni you want to see when\nyou look at me. I just want to protect you.
And a specter of the past can't do that.\nOnly I—as I am right now—can.

I'm so sorry. We spent so long together,
and I never realized what it was you
wanted. For a thousand years, I've been
nothing but my own special brand of idiot.
I've been useless to you, right to the bitter\nend. Even so...it's like a weight has been\nlifted from my chest at last.
Are you going to leave me again?\nYou can't! I won't accept it.\nDon't...don't leave me alone!
